# Array vs ArrayList

| Array            | ArrayList       |
| ---------------- | --------------- |
| Fixed Size       | Dynamic Size    |
| Faster           | Slightly Slower |
| Stores same type | Stores Objects  |
| Length Property  | size() Method   |

---

# Advantages of Arrays

1. Easy storage of multiple values.
2. Fast access using index.
3. Efficient memory usage.
4. Useful in sorting and searching algorithms.

---

# Disadvantages of Arrays

1. Fixed size.
2. Cannot grow dynamically.
3. Insertion and deletion are costly.
4. Stores only same type of elements.

